cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.CL 

The paper discusses the use of machine learning algorithms to optimize optimization algorithms, which falls under the category of meta-learning. The paper specifically focuses on tasks related to machine learning, such as training neural networks and styling images with neural art, which suggests that the paper is likely to be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of LSTMs also suggests that the paper may be categorized under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the paper discusses the application of the learned optimization algorithms to computer vision tasks (styling images with neural art), which suggests that it may also be categorized under cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
